profile_positions.description:
Responsible for all global online marketing activities for Philips Television products.
Develop and implement central online marketing plans and calendar that fit the overall marketing objectives of the company in order to grow the business through the online channel.
Identifying and driving continued online improvements to enhance all aspects of the customer journey resulting in increased conversion on- and offline.

- Define global online strategy and deployment to +20 country organizations
- Driving digital maturity within the company;
- Building and maintaining close relationships with country organizations. Ensuring effective handover of centrally developed assets for local activation;
- Brief and manage external parties; agencies, Philips IT to create online tools, websites that support all aspects of the customer journey;
- Safeguarding the application of Philips brand guidelines across all online touch points;
- Continuous improvement of www.philips.com/tv;
- Annual phase-in Philips TV product range through execution of world-class rich content assets on own website, pure-play and brick-and-click retail partner sites;
- Creation of social media strategy and deployment package for local activation, focusing on advocacy building +20 countries;
- Driving the social media strategy within the countries for Facebook, YouTube, Instagram, to ensure a consistent messaging and brand identity across the countries. Total Facebook community increase from 69K to 1 million in 1.5 years;
- Create and deploy monthly content calendars for Facebook towards the countries, development of YouTube pre-rolls, Instagram competitions, social campaign IFA event;
- Campaign management; twice a year, tactical and branding; 
- SEA;
- SEO;
- eCRM;
- Planning, execution and budgeting of all online projects;
- Work close with countries, marketing managers, product managers, consumer care, external agencies, IT;
- Analyze, monitor online KPIs, reporting and evaluation of online performance.

Owning key online projects and processes within the BG television, all based on the business objectives of the BG, reporting to the senior online manager.

•	Responsible for the operational (day-to-day) running of Philips Television product content on Philips.com and the navigational paths thereto;
•	Working with the country organizations to ensure that rich content also reaches the retail websites;.  
•	Monitor and report on the performance of Philips.com and online retailer websites and build continuous improvement plans;
•	Act as an online competence/ ambassador by sharing online knowledge and building up competencies inside the BG;
